You know, I don't watch remembrance shows to see who died.  I watch to remember there are still hero's.  I watch to have faith in my neighbors and in people in general.  I will never be a hero.  I am glad to be alive too, but I think you have a mistaken understanding of the word "empathy."  I can imagine that I was there.  I can imagine that my life relied on the heroes who ran into danger when everyone was just trying to get out.<br>
