&lt;Anlah'Shok&gt;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ujexielia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jexielia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 983<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/11/02 9:35:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3618.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Happy 9/11 day everyone!</span><hr size=1> I dont want to sound insensitive but all day its bothered me, and I read this post when it had only one response and it didnt bother me it actually went along with a lot of what I saw today...<br>
<br>
I live in Michigan, far away from New York, Pennsylvania, Washington... far away from where the events took place... though watching on television was like being there and the pain and the fear was as real as could be, I was in the comfort of my livingroom, safe with my family.  I will forever be grateful for that.<br>
<br>
Today, 9-11-2002, I watched people take the day off from work to "remember the victims, remember the hero's" as if it were a holiday... someone said once to "carry on, we are a strong nation".  They never once said "forget about it, get over it, move on" but c'mon I dont see why this ONE day is the day where people want to fly their flags, and have a moment of silence, and light a candle, and remember...<br>
<br>
I remember ever day.<br>
<br>
This day, today, isnt any more significant than one week ago, or a week from now.  Every day I walk through my livingroom and I have a huge huge black and gold picture of the New York sky line... as many times as I stop and look at that picture sometimes I can see the images of the buildings falling, the people, the tears, the fear, the horror... I dont need to have an anniversary, a celebration, ONE day to remember that our nation, our world, had to see such horror.<br>
<br>
We shouldnt take the date of the event to look back and remember what happened... we shouldnt take one day of the year to think about the heros of our nation... we shouldnt take one day to love our neighbors and forget about who made us mad and why... we shouldnt take one day to shed a tear and remember the tragedy and the losses... we shouldnt let one day be the only day to signify the firefighters, the policemen, the hero's, the donors, the victims... <br>
<br>
9-11 is not a holiday... and too many people, imho, acted like it was.  Perhaps thats where the sarcasm came from.  I was very angry today that so many people acted like today was more important than any other... its not.<br>
<br>
Every morning I turn on my radio and listen to the "funny" morning show... today I had to hear the news all over again, I listened as they went through it all over again... the plane crash, the second plane crash, the buildings collapsing, the flight conversations, the discovery of the plane that crashed in PA... I had to listen to it all over again... that didnt help me at all, it doesnt make me feel better, it doesnt make me feel worse, it doesnt make me feel as if I should go out and hug a firefighter, it doesnt make me feel any different than I felt a week ago... it just hurt to have to live it over again.  It made me angry that our nation took "today" and made it a day for broadcasters to gain ratings, a day for car dealerships to broadcast commercials to "remember the victims and the heros"... <br>
<br>
We should remember ever day how lucky we are... we should remember every day how our lives can change in a heartbeat... we should remember every day how important our hero's are...<br>
<br>
 <p><font color=yellow>~Jexielia~</font><br>
